page.title: 19Birds in Stickney.
page.content: Many different kinds of birds are in Stickney,mostly in the picnic area.The common garden birds are robins, blackbirds, blue-tits, great-tits, starlings, song thrushes, bullfinches and chaffinches. These stay in Great Britain all the year round. Some birds are summer visitors, such as swallows, house martins, and sand martins. There are also birds of prey found in Stickney. These are kestrels, barn owls and kites. Sometimes an osprey can be seen when it is migrating. Many kinds of birds that live on the water are seen here too.These are swans, wild geese, moorhens and different types of gulls.
